documentation.value:
Outputs one or more expressions, with no additional newline or space.

```php
echo 'Hello, World!';
echo $name, ' is ', $age;
echo "Value: {$var}";
```

Outputs a string. Unlike echo, print accepts only one argument and always returns 1.

```php
print 'Hello, World!';
print("Value: $var");
$result = print 'test';
```

Displays structured information about one or more expressions including its type and value.

```php
var_dump($variable);
var_dump($arr, $obj, $bool);
var_dump(['a' => 1, 'b' => 2]);
```

Prints human-readable information about a variable. Especially useful for arrays and objects.

```php
print_r($array);
$output = print_r($array, true);
print_r(['name' => 'John', 'age' => 30]);
```

Outputs or returns a parsable string representation of a variable.

```php
var_export($array);
$code = var_export($array, true);
var_export(['key' => 'value']);
```

Outputs a formatted string using format specifiers.

```php
printf('Name: %s, Age: %d', $name, $age);
printf('Price: $%.2f', $price);
printf('%05d', $number);
```

Returns a formatted string without outputting it.

```php
$msg = sprintf('Hello, %s!', $name);
$price = sprintf('$%.2f', 19.99);
$padded = sprintf('%05d', 42);
```

Returns the length of the given string in bytes.

```php
$len = strlen('Hello'); // 5
$len = strlen($str);
if (strlen($input) > 0) { ... }
```

Finds the position of the first occurrence of a substring in a string.

```php
$pos = strpos('Hello World', 'World'); // 6
if (strpos($haystack, $needle) !== false) { ... }
$pos = strpos($str, 'x', 5);
```

Returns the portion of string specified by the offset and length parameters.

```php
$part = substr('Hello World', 0, 5); // 'Hello'
$last = substr($str, -3);
$rest = substr($str, 6);
```

Replaces all occurrences of the search string with the replacement string.

```php
$result = str_replace('world', 'PHP', 'Hello world');
$clean = str_replace([' ', '-'], '_', $str);
$result = str_replace($search, $replace, $subject, $count);
```

Determines if a string contains a given substring.

```php
if (str_contains('Hello World', 'World')) { ... }
if (str_contains($haystack, $needle)) { ... }
```

Checks if a string starts with a given substring.

```php
if (str_starts_with($url, 'https://')) { ... }
if (str_starts_with($line, '#')) { ... }
```

Checks if a string ends with a given substring.

```php
if (str_ends_with($file, '.php')) { ... }
if (str_ends_with($url, '/')) { ... }
```

Splits a string by a string delimiter and returns an array.

```php
$parts = explode(',', 'a,b,c'); // ['a', 'b', 'c']
$words = explode(' ', $sentence);
$parts = explode('/', $path, 3);
```

Joins array elements with a glue string.

```php
$str = implode(', ', ['a', 'b', 'c']); // 'a, b, c'
$csv = implode(',', $values);
$path = implode('/', $segments);
```

Repeats a string a given number of times.

```php
$line = str_repeat('-', 40);
$indent = str_repeat('  ', $level);
```

Inserts HTML line breaks before all newlines in a string.

```php
$html = nl2br("Hello\nWorld");
echo nl2br($text);
```

Converts special characters to HTML entities for safe output.

```php
$safe = htmlspecialchars($input, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8');
echo htmlspecialchars($userInput);
```

Encodes the given data with Base64.

```php
$encoded = base64_encode('Hello World');
$encoded = base64_encode($binaryData);
```

Decodes a Base64-encoded string.

```php
$decoded = base64_decode($encoded);
$data = base64_decode($base64String, true);
```

Pops and returns the last element of the array, shortening it by one.

```php
$last = array_pop($stack);
$item = array_pop($arr);
```

Prepends one or more elements to the beginning of an array.

```php
array_unshift($arr, 'first');
array_unshift($arr, 'a', 'b');
```

Merges one or more arrays. Values with numeric keys are re-indexed; string keys are overwritten.

```php
$merged = array_merge($arr1, $arr2);
$all = array_merge($a, $b, $c);
```

Creates an array by using one array for keys and another for its values.

```php
$result = array_combine(['a', 'b', 'c'], [1, 2, 3]);
// ['a' => 1, 'b' => 2, 'c' => 3]
```

Applies the callback to the elements of the given arrays and returns a new array.

```php
$doubled = array_map(fn($n) => $n * 2, [1, 2, 3]);
$upper = array_map('strtoupper', $words);
```

Searches the array for a given value and returns the corresponding key if found.

```php
$key = array_search('apple', $fruits);
if (($key = array_search($val, $arr)) !== false) { ... }
```

Returns the values from a single column in a multi-dimensional array.

```php
$names = array_column($users, 'name');
$indexed = array_column($records, 'value', 'key');
```

Counts all elements in an array or a Countable object.

```php
$total = count($arr);
$depth = count($matrix, COUNT_RECURSIVE);
if (count($items) > 0) { ... }
```

Sorts an array in place in ascending order.

```php
sort($arr);
sort($numbers, SORT_NUMERIC);
```

Sorts an array in place in descending order.

```php
rsort($arr);
rsort($numbers, SORT_NUMERIC);
```

Sorts an array by values using a user-defined comparison function.

```php
usort($arr, fn($a, $b) => $a - $b);
usort($users, fn($a, $b) => strcmp($a['name'], $b['name']));
```

Checks if the given key or index exists in the array.

```php
if (array_key_exists('name', $data)) { ... }
if (array_key_exists(0, $arr)) { ... }
```

Creates an array containing variables and their values.

```php
$name = 'John';
$age = 30;
$data = compact('name', 'age'); // ['name' => 'John', 'age' => 30]
```

Import variables into the current symbol table from an array.

```php
$data = ['name' => 'John', 'age' => 30];
extract($data);
echo $name; // 'John'
```

Creates an array containing a range of elements.

```php
$nums = range(1, 10); // [1,2,3,...,10]
$letters = range('a', 'z');
$evens = range(0, 20, 2);
```

Counts all the values of an array and returns an associative array.

```php
$counts = array_count_values(['a','b','a','c','b','a']);
// ['a' => 3, 'b' => 2, 'c' => 1]
```

Reads entire file into a string. Preferred way to read the contents of a file into a string.

```php
$content = file_get_contents('file.txt');
$html = file_get_contents('https://example.com');
$json = file_get_contents('data.json');
```

Write data to a file. Identical to calling fopen(), fwrite(), and fclose() successively.

```php
file_put_contents('file.txt', $data);
file_put_contents('log.txt', $msg, FILE_APPEND);
```

Opens a file or URL and returns a file pointer resource.

```php
$fp = fopen('file.txt', 'r');
$fp = fopen('output.csv', 'w');
$fp = fopen('log.txt', 'a');
```

Reads up to length bytes from a file pointer.

```php
$data = fread($fp, filesize('file.txt'));
$chunk = fread($handle, 1024);
```

Writes the contents of string to the file stream pointed to by handle.

```php
fwrite($fp, 'Hello World');
fwrite($handle, $data, strlen($data));
```

Gets a line from file pointer.

```php
while (($line = fgets($fp)) !== false) {
    echo $line;
}
```

Checks whether a file or directory exists.

```php
if (file_exists('config.php')) { ... }
if (file_exists($path)) { ... }
```

Deletes a file.

```php
unlink('temp.txt');
if (file_exists($file)) { unlink($file); }
```

Finds pathnames matching a pattern.

```php
$phpFiles = glob('*.php');
$files = glob('src/**/*.php');
```

Lists files and directories inside the specified path.

```php
$files = scandir('/path/to/dir');
$files = scandir('.', SCANDIR_SORT_DESCENDING);
```

Returns information about a file path as an associative array.

```php
$info = pathinfo('/var/www/index.php');
// ['dirname'=>'/var/www','basename'=>'index.php','extension'=>'php','filename'=>'index']
```

Returns the canonicalized absolute pathname.

```php
$real = realpath('./relative/path');
$real = realpath(__DIR__ . '/../config');
```

Returns the JSON representation of a value.

```php
$json = json_encode(['name' => 'John', 'age' => 30]);
$json = json_encode($data, JSON_PRETTY_PRINT);
$json = json_encode($obj, JSON_UNESCAPED_UNICODE);
```

Generates cryptographically secure pseudo-random integers.

```php
$num = random_int(1, 100);
$token = random_int(100000, 999999);
```

Determines if a variable is declared and is different than null.

```php
if (isset($var)) { ... }
if (isset($arr['key'])) { ... }
if (isset($a, $b, $c)) { ... } // all must be set
```

Destroys the specified variables.

```php
unset($var);
unset($arr['key']);
unset($a, $b, $c);
```

Determines whether a variable is considered empty. A variable is empty if it doesn't exist or its value equals false.

```php
if (empty($var)) { ... }
if (!empty($arr)) { ... }
```

Defines a class with properties, methods, and optional constructor.

```php
class User {
    public function __construct(
        private string $name,
        private int $age,
    ) {}

    public function getName(): string {
        return $this->name;
    }
}
```

Defines an interface that classes can implement.

```php
interface Loggable {
    public function log(string $message): void;
}
```

Defines a trait for horizontal code reuse.

```php
trait HasTimestamps {
    public DateTime $createdAt;
    public DateTime $updatedAt;
}
```

Defines an abstract class that cannot be instantiated directly.

```php
abstract class Shape {
    abstract public function area(): float;

    public function describe(): string {
        return 'Area: ' . $this->area();
    }
}
```

Defines an enumeration, a restrictive type with a fixed set of possible values.

```php
enum Status: string {
    case Active = 'active';
    case Inactive = 'inactive';
    case Pending = 'pending';
}
```

Defines a public method accessible from anywhere.

```php
public function getName(): string
{
    return $this->name;
}
```

Defines a private method accessible only within the declaring class.

```php
private function validate(): bool
{
    return $this->value > 0;
}
```

Defines a protected method accessible within the class and its subclasses.

```php
protected function process(): void
{
    // ...
}
```

Defines the constructor, called when an object is created.

```php
public function __construct(
    private string $name,
    private int $age = 0,
) {}
```

Called when there are no more references to an object or during shutdown.

```php
public function __destruct()
{
    fclose($this->handle);
}
```

Called when an object is converted to a string.

```php
public function __toString(): string
{
    return $this->name;
}
```

Called when reading inaccessible or non-existing properties.

```php
public function __get(string $name): mixed
{
    return $this->data[$name] ?? null;
}
```

Called when writing to inaccessible or non-existing properties.

```php
public function __set(string $name, mixed $value): void
{
    $this->data[$name] = $value;
}
```

Called when invoking inaccessible methods in an object context.

```php
public function __call(string $name, array $arguments): mixed
{
    // ...
}
```

Called when invoking inaccessible methods in a static context.

```php
public static function __callStatic(string $name, array $arguments): mixed
{
    // ...
}
```

Called when a script tries to call an object as a function.

```php
public function __invoke(mixed ...$args): mixed
{
    return $this->handle(...$args);
}
```

Declares a property that can only be initialized once.

```php
class User {
    public function __construct(
        public readonly string $name,
        public readonly int $id,
    ) {}
}
```

Evaluates a subject and returns a value based on an identity check.

```php
$result = match($status) {
    'active' => 'Active',
    'inactive', 'disabled' => 'Inactive',
    default => 'Unknown',
};
```

Parses an English textual date/time description into a Unix timestamp.

```php
$ts = strtotime('next Monday');
$ts = strtotime('+1 week');
$ts = strtotime('2024-12-31');
```

Creates a new DateTime object representing the specified date and time.

```php
$now = new DateTime();
$date = new DateTime('2024-01-15');
$date = new DateTime('tomorrow');
```

Creates an immutable DateTime object. Modification methods return a new instance.

```php
$now = new DateTimeImmutable();
$date = new DateTimeImmutable('2024-01-15 14:30:00');
$tomorrow = $date->modify('+1 day');
```

Outputs a message and terminates the current script. Equivalent to exit.

```php
die('Fatal error occurred');
$result or die('Failed');
```

Send a raw HTTP header. Must be called before any output.

```php
header('Content-Type: application/json');
header('Location: /dashboard');
header('HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found');
```

Sends a cookie. Must be called before any output.

```php
setcookie('name', 'value', time() + 3600);
setcookie('user', $name, [
    'expires' => time() + 86400,
    'path' => '/',
    'secure' => true,
    'httponly' => true,
]);
```

Copies a file.

```php
copy('source.txt', 'dest.txt');
if (copy($src, $dst)) { echo 'Copied'; }
```

Renames a file or directory.

```php
rename('old.txt', 'new.txt');
rename($oldPath, $newPath);
```

Generates cryptographically secure pseudo-random bytes.

```php
$bytes = random_bytes(32);
$hex = bin2hex(random_bytes(16));
```

Sets the type of a variable.

```php
settype($var, 'integer');
settype($val, 'string');
```

Creates a new instance of a class.

```php
$obj = new ClassName();
$user = new User('John', 30);
$date = new DateTime();
```

A class can inherit methods and properties from another class using extends.

```php
class Admin extends User {
    // ...
}
```

A class can implement one or more interfaces.

```php
class Logger implements LoggerInterface {
    // ...
}
```

Declares class members (properties or methods) as accessible without needing an instantiation.

```php
class Counter {
    public static int $count = 0;

    public static function increment(): void {
        self::$count++;
    }
}
```

Creates a new DateTime object. Procedural alias of DateTime::__construct.

```php
$date = date_create('2024-01-15');
$now = date_create();
```

Returns a DateInterval representing the difference between two DateTime objects.

```php
$diff = date_diff($date1, $date2);
echo $diff->days . ' days';
```
